{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778976383463,"sessionID":"ses_1ccbfceb9ffenpdxiMuCe2grdL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_N5sWpwyO9Jk18BUGyXhCax5K","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://dentaleducationhub.com/surfaces-of-the-teeth/","format":"markdown","timeout":30},"output":"    Surfaces of the Teeth: A review of Dental Anatomy | Dental Education Hub                           \n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Blue-Minimalist-Tooth-Illustration-Dentist-Logo-1.png)\n\n-   [Home](https://dentaleducationhub.com)\n-   [About us](https://dentaleducationhub.com/about-us/)\n-   [Blogs](#)\n-   [YouTube Video](https://dentaleducationhub.com/youtube-video/)\n-   [Contact Us](https://dentaleducationhub.com/contact-us/)\n\n# Surfaces of the Teeth: A review of Dental Anatomy\n\nby [RizwanUllah](https://dentaleducationhub.com/author/rizwanullah2019/ \"Posts by RizwanUllah\") | Mar 31, 2020 | [Dental Anatomy](https://dentaleducationhub.com/category/dental-anatomy/) | [9 comments](https://dentaleducationhub.com/surfaces-of-the-teeth/#respond)\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/tooth-surfaces-1024x538.jpg)\n\nThe understanding and correct use of basic dental terminologies are crucial not only in the initial academic years but also in clinical practice, dental laboratory settings, and research. There are mainly five surfaces of the teeth.\n\n  \nThe five surfaces are labial, palatal, mesial, distal and incisal surfaces. For example, in posterior [teeth](https://dentaleducationhub.com/structure-of-human-teeth-and-their-functions/), mandibular molar, the five surfaces are buccal, occlusal, lingual, mesial, and distal surfaces. The names are given to these surfaces according to their position and use.\n\n  \nFollowing is a brief description of this topic. The blog will cover all aspects you want to read. It includes but is not limited to the explanation of all surfaces. A video and images are also part of it for better understanding.\n\n## Types: Surfaces of the Teeth\n\n### **Labial Surface**\n\nThe surface of the tooth that is towards or adjacent to the lips. The term labial surface is usually used for surfaces of incisors and canines that are present just adjacent to the lips.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Labial-Surfaces-300x283.jpg)\n\n**Clinical picture showing the labial surfaces**\n\n###  **Buccal Surface**\n\nThe tooth’s surface is towards or adjacent to the mucosa of the cheek. The term buccal surface is designated for the surfaces of premolars and molars that are immediately adjacent to the cheek.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Buccal-Surfaces--300x285.jpg)\n\n **Clinical picture**\n\n### **Facial Surfaces**\n\nThe labial and the buccal surfaces are collectively referred to as facial surfaces of [teeth](https://dentaleducationhub.com/structure-of-human-teeth-and-their-functions/).  \n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Facial-Surfaces--300x261.jpg)\n\n**Plaster model showing the facial surfaces (Labial + Buccal surfaces = Facial surfaces)**\n\n### **Palatal Surface**\n\nThe surface that is towards or adjacent to the palate is the palatal surface. The term palatal surface is used for surfaces of maxillary teeth (both anterior and posterior teeth) that are towards or adjacent to the palate.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Palatal-surfaces-300x242.jpg)\n\n **Clinical picture (Red arrows= Palatal surfaces)**\n\n###  **Lingual Surface**\n\nThe surface of the tooth that is towards or adjacent to the tongue. The term lingual surface is used for the surface of a mandibular tooth (anterior or posterior) that is present immediately adjacent to the tongue.   \n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Lingual-and-occlusal-Surfaces--300x240.jpg)\n\n**Clinical picture showing lingual and occlusal surfaces (Red arrows=Lingual surfaces)**\n\n### **Mesial Surface**\n\nThe surface of the tooth towards or near the midline is the mesial surface. The only teeth that share their mesial surfaces are the maxillary and the [mandibular central incisors](https://dentaleducationhub.com/permanent-mandibular-central-incisor/).\n\n### **Distal Surface**\n\nThe surface of the tooth that is away from the midline is the distal surface.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mesial-distal-and-Incisal-surfaces-300x196.jpg)\n\n**Clinical picture showing mesial and distal surfaces of the central incisor (Green arrow= Mesial , and Orange arrow=Distal surface)**\n\n### **Proximal Surface**\n\nThe mesial and distal surfaces are collectively called proximal surfaces. In other words, the proximal surface means either the mesial or the distal surface.\n\n### **Incisal Surface**\n\nThe cutting surfaces of anterior teeth (both upper and lower anterior teeth) are known as incisal surfaces.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mesial-distal-and-Incisal-surfaces-300x196.jpg)\n\n**Clinical picture showing incisal surface (Pink arrow= Incisal surface)**\n\n### **Occlusal Surface**\n\nThe biting or grinding surfaces of posterior teeth (premolars and molars) are referred to as occlusal surfaces.\n\n![](https://dentaleducationhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Lingual-and-occlusal-Surfaces--300x240.jpg)\n\n**Clinical picture showing lingual and occlusal surfaces (Black arrows= Occlusal surfaces)**\n\n**Tooth Surface**\n\n**Description**\n\nLabial Surface\n\nSurface of the tooth towards the lips\n\nBuccal Surface\n\nSurface of the tooth towards the buccal mucosa\n\nFacial Surface\n\nLabial and buccal surfaces collectively called facial surfaces\n\nPalatal Surface\n\nSurface of the tooth towards the palate\n\nLingual Surface\n\nSurface of the tooth towards the tongue\n\nMesial Surface\n\nSurface of tooth towards the midline\n\nDistal Surface\n\nSurface of tooth away from midline\n\nProximal Surface\n\nMesial and distal surface collectively called proximal surface\n\nIncisal Surface\n\nCutting surface of anterior teeth\n\nOcclusal Surface\n\nGrinding surface of posterior teeth\n\n**Table: Tooth surfaces chart for rapid review**\n\n### Surfaces of Teeth | Video Explanation\n\n[← Previous Post](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tooth-extraction-aftercare-an-ultimate-guide/)[Next Post →](https://dentaleducationhub.com/how-to-draw-teeth/)\n\n[Labial Surface](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tag/labial-surface/) , [Lingual Surface](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tag/lingual-surface/) , [Occlusal Surface](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tag/occlusal-surface/) , [Palatal Surface](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tag/palatal-surface/) , [Surfaces of the Teeth](https://dentaleducationhub.com/tag/surfaces-of-the-teeth/)\n\n![](https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ce806168bf1171359b9ef9b2759145a26906a812ae794864c77594ef9f546766?s=96&d=mm&r=g)\n\nAbout RizwanUllah\n\n## 0 Comments\n\n### Submit a Comment [Cancel reply](/surfaces-of-the-teeth/#respond)\n\nYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked \\*\n\nComment \\*\n\nName \\* \n\nEmail \\* \n\nWebsite \n\n Save my name, email, and website in this browser for the next time I comment.\n\nSubmit Comment  \n\nSearch for:  \n\n#### Recent Posts\n\n-   [Dental Wax Knife](https://dentaleducationhub.com/dental-wax-knife/)\n-   [Lecron Dental Wax Carver](https://dentaleducationhub.com/lecron-dental-wax-carver/)\n-   [Learning Dentistry is Fun with Rememberology Dental Mnemonics](https://dentaleducationhub.com/learning-dentistry-is-fun-with-rememberology-dental-mnemonics/)\n-   [Deciduous Mandibular Second Molar](https://dentaleducationhub.com/deciduous-mandibular-second-molar/)\n-   [Deciduous Mandibular First Molar](https://dentaleducationhub.com/deciduous-mandibular-first-molar/)\n\n \n\nContact Us","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://dentaleducationhub.com/surfaces-of-the-teeth/ (text/html; charset=UTF-8)","time":{"start":1778976379055,"end":1778976383461}},"id":"prt_e334150a9001cVMDH2f5CSq1d1","sessionID":"ses_1ccbfceb9ffenpdxiMuCe2grdL","messageID":"msg_e33413b39001gi7vRxPerAIO9B"}}
